@pchote

> I guess my only real concern is that these maps skew quite hard towards symmetric team maps. I think it would be good if we can include some additional assymetrical/scenic/ffa maps to balance these out a bit.

They do, because most of the experienced players like to play these maps, but as I've said I'm okay with not removing some of the maps that are already there. Which ones should remain, in your opinion?

@pchote

> Are there any other good new maps that we can include for these? (from the two map contests?)

Those maps are awful though.

@Micr0Bit

>additionally rules get approved by a group of people that play mostly 1v1's , giving the team-game aspect almost no attention

Most of the maps I have added are team maps. Most of the games that are being played in TD multiplayer are pretty big 3v3 or 4v4 maps. I don't know what you're talking about here.

@dtluna : you dont need to feel accused , its just a general observation

>i feel the same for RA , "some" people think its necessary to replace every map with a strict balanced version of it (or even a new map) where every spot and ore-patch should be mirrored

^ "this" was more directed towards TD, now that we have another great overhaul of a official map-pool   (the teamplay-aspect was more for RA alone , cause i dont have any idea about TD's balance)
